text:
So many (good) surprises and an amazing performance!
First, I was surprised about the short anime. It was really good! But I didn't expect that you would go into that kind of direction :_GuraMM:
Then, I was surprised by you doing basically Rhythm Heaven on stage :_GuraHAHA:
And then you sing Chichi wo moge with Shion!?!? :_Sometimes: :_OHH::_NYO:

But these (very Gura) surprises aside, the songs were really good, it was awesome to see you dance in 3D and the guests were a perfect match! We knew that Okayu is a big Gura fan and Gura also likes Okayu and her song, so this pairing was just perfect. Her wife, Shion, had to be there as well of course! And the song with Umi-C was also very fitting. I bet Gura really wanted to include some Vocaloid songs because she knows them and the dances very well!
Didn't expect Kronii though, I thought there would be one song with Calli (like Q). But it was great nonetheless - I love My Soul, Your Beats!

I think you can be very proud of this 3D live and we can all be proud of you :_BloopYAY: thank you for everything, Goomba!! :_WuvXob:

text: I'm so glad I've been here since day one. This live was absolutely incredible in its own right, but knowing the goofy, nervous little shark we met two years ago is the same idol shining on that stage, and remembering so many moments where we watched her grow to become who she is today...you're an inspiration, Goob. I'm so proud of you. And more than anything, thank you so much for being YOU, and sharing that with us. Your weird or random interests, your unique and honest way of thinking, your dreams and your worries, your sense of humor that is sometimes a little and maybe sometimes a lot yabai; there are plenty of amazing idols out there, for all sorts of people. But there could only ever be one Gwar G. Gumbo, and I'm really glad you're here.
